1. The hello router accepts HTTP/1.0 requests and returns different responses based on the request method and path.
2. For a GET request to the root path, the router returns HTTP 200 with a greeting body.
3. For a GET request to the /ping path, the router returns HTTP 200 with the body "pong".
4. For any other request, the router returns HTTP 404 with the body "not found".
5. The service listens on port 18889 and reads up to 4096 bytes per incoming request.
